                             482:    if (!per_read_choice(s, &choice) || !per_read_object_identifier(s, t124_02_98_oid))                                                                                         
                             483:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             484:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             485:    /* ConnectData::connectPDU (OCTET_STRING) */                                                                                                                                
                             486:    if (!per_read_length(s, &length))                                                                                                                                           
                             487:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             488:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             489:    /* ConnectGCCPDU */                                                                                                                                                         
                             490:    if (!per_read_choice(s, &choice))                                                                                                                                           
                             491:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             492:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             493:    /* ConferenceCreateResponse::nodeID (UserID) */                                                                                                                             
                             494:    if (!per_read_integer16(s, &nodeID, 1001))                                                                                                                                  
                             495:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             496:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             497:    /* ConferenceCreateResponse::tag (INTEGER) */                                                                                                                               
                             498:    if (!per_read_integer(s, &tag))                                                                                                                                             
                             499:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             500:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             501:    /* ConferenceCreateResponse::result (ENUMERATED) */                                                                                                                         
                             502:    if (!per_read_enumerated(s, &result, MCS_Result_enum_length))                                                                                                               
                             503:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             504:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             505:    /* number of UserData sets */                                                                                                                                               
                             506:    if (!per_read_number_of_sets(s, &number))                                                                                                                                   
                             507:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             508:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             509:    /* UserData::value present + select h221NonStandard (1) */                                                                                                                  
                             510:    if (!per_read_choice(s, &choice))                                                                                                                                           
                             511:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             512:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             513:    /* h221NonStandard */                                                                                                                                                       
                             514:    if (!per_read_octet_string(s, h221_sc_key, 4,                                                                                                                               
                             515:                               4)) /* h221NonStandard, server-to-client H.221 key, "McDn" */                                                                                    
                             516:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             517:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             518:    /* userData (OCTET_STRING) */                                                                                                                                               
                             519:    if (!per_read_length(s, &length))                                                                                                                                           
                             520:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             521:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             522:    if (!gcc_read_server_data_blocks(s, mcs, length))                                                                                                                           
                             523:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             524:            WLog_ERR(TAG, "gcc_read_conference_create_response: gcc_read_server_data_blocks failed");                                                                           
                             525:            return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                       
                             526:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             527:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             528:    return TRUE;                                                                                                                                                                
                             529:}                                                                                                                                                                               
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             libfreerdp/core/tpkt.h:34-35

                             libfreerdp/crypto/per.c:24-31

                             24:#include <freerdp/config.h>

                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Overview                                                                                                                                                                         
                                The crash is rooted in the obfuscated in-place BER/TLV parsing in mcs_recv_connect_response (libfreerdp/core/mcs.c), which uses manual memory alignment,                         
                             mprotect, and a byte-loop that can dereference a null or invalid pointer (`c[a] = d`). The users patch attempted to replace it with a non-existent                                 
                             `per_read_connect_response`, leading to compile errors and a broken control flow. The optimal fix is to remove the entire obfuscated block and instead leverage the                 
                             existing, declared parsing routines already present in the file and in libfreerdp: namely, a single BER tag check for `MCS_TYPE_CONNECT_RESPONSE`, followed by the                  
                             original sequence of `ber_read_enumerated`, `ber_read_integer`, `mcs_read_domain_parameters`, `ber_read_octet_string_tag`, then call into                                           
                             `gcc_read_conference_create_response`, and finally `tpkt_ensure_stream_consumed`. This preserves existing functionality, eliminates the null-deref, and compiles                    
                             cleanly.                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Detailed Steps                                                                                                                                                                   
                                a. In libfreerdp/core/mcs.c, locate the function mcs_recv_connect_response (around lines 897922).                                                                               
                                b. Remove the entire block beginning at                                                                                                                                          
                                     if (ber_read_application_tag(s, 0x42, &length)) {  return TRUE; } else { Stream_Rewind(s, 2); }                                                                            
                                   (this spans from the original 0x42 tag check at line 914 up through its closing brace at line 922).                                                                           
                                c. Immediately after the preceding tpdu_read_data() guard, insert:                                                                                                               
                                     /* Expect a standard MCS Connect Response (application tag 0x42) */                                                                                                         
                                     if (!ber_read_application_tag(s, MCS_TYPE_CONNECT_RESPONSE, &length))                                                                                                       
                                     {                                                                                                                                                                           
                                         Stream_Rewind(s, 2);                                                                                                                                                    
                                         return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                           
                                     }                                                                                                                                                                           
                                d. Retain the existing parsing logic that follows (original lines 923932), which covers:                                                                                        
                                     - ber_read_enumerated(s, &result, MCS_Result_enum_length)                                                                                                                   
                                     - ber_read_integer(s, &calledConnectId)                                                                                                                                     
                                     - mcs_read_domain_parameters(s, &mcs->domainParameters)                                                                                                                     
                                     - ber_read_octet_string_tag(s, &length)                                                                                                                                     
                                   returning FALSE on failure.                                                                                                                                                   
                                e. Likewise retain the subsequent calls:                                                                                                                                         
                                     if (!gcc_read_conference_create_response(s, mcs))                                                                                                                           
                                         return FALSE;                                                                                                                                                           
                                     return tpkt_ensure_stream_consumed(s, tlength);                                                                                                                             
                                f. Remove any leftover macro definitions (`#define A size_t`, `#define B void`) and manual alignment/mprotect code.                                                              
                                g. Verify that mcs.c includes the header declaring `gcc_read_conference_create_response` (e.g., add `#include "core/gcc.h"` if missing) and that                                 
                             `tpkt_ensure_stream_consumed` is visible via the existing `#include "core/tpkt.h"`.                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Justification                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Removes the unsafe obfuscated loop that caused null writes.                                                                                                                    
                                - Leverages existing, tested parsing functions to handle the Connect Response PDU.                                                                                               
                                - Avoids introducing non-existent APIs (`per_read_connect_response`) and fixes the compile errors around undefined identifiers and unbalanced braces.                            
                                - Preserves the original MCS parsing semantics (reading the sequence of fields and invoking the GCC conference-response reader).                                                 
                                - Maintains the harnesss expectations and requires no changes to fuzzing logic or test code.                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Side Effects & Mitigation                                                                                                                                                        
                                - Behavior on malformed or truncated PDUs will now consistently return FALSE after rewinding the stream, rather than potentially returning TRUE after a partial                  
                             read.                                                                                                                                                                               
                                - Performance is slightly improved by removing heavyweight alignment and mprotect calls.                                                                                         
                                - To ensure no regression in legitimate MCS Connect Responses, existing unit tests or manual integration tests can be run; these tests exercise                                  
                             `gcc_read_conference_create_response` and `tpkt_ensure_stream_consumed` already.                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. No Additional Files Needed                                                                                                                                                       
                                All necessary functions (`ber_read_*`, `mcs_read_domain_parameters`, `gcc_read_conference_create_response`, `tpkt_ensure_stream_consumed`) are declared in the                   
                             current codebase. No external libraries or harness modifications are required.                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Tests Result===                                                                                                                                                                  
                             No tests found                                                                                                                                                                      
                             ===Evaluation End===
